{backimage bg.iff}
{def}
{left}
{bold}PowerPC Compatibility Libraries{nobold}
{pp}
ppc.library - PowerUP compatibility layer{p}
WOSEmu - WarpUP compatibility layer
{pp}
{pp}
{bold}Exec{nobold}
{pp}
Mixed mode allowing 68k and PPC code running in the same task. No exception and
no task-switch to go from one mode to the other one.
{pp}
Task memory pool{p}
Better multithreading support{p}
SystemV ABI support, using fpu registers for system functions is possible{p}
New functions to get and set tasks states (stack, priority...).{p}
New functions for better memory handling
{pp}
{bold}graphics.library{nobold}
{pp}
RTG{p}
New functions for alpha blending,{p}
Special visual effects (used by Ambient...){p}
True colour{p}
Extended draw primitives.
{pp}
{bold}diskfont.library{nobold}
{pp}
Anti-aliased fonts in development{p}
FreeType2 - Vector fonts library{p}
Supports Type0, Type1, Type42, TrueType, and OpenType fonts.{p}
Anti-aliasing support
{pp}
{bold}Datatypes{nobold}
{pp}
Datatypes are a means of allowing programs to handle different data formats without having to
directly support them themselves.
{pp}
Currently supported:
{pp}
JFIF-JPEG{p}
PNG{p}
IFF-ILBM{p}
BMP{p}
GIF{p}
PCX{p}
PBM{p}
Icons{p}
Text{p}
Binary
{pp}
More in development.
{pp}
{bold}Shell and Console{nobold}
{pp}
Improved resident commands{p}
* If: New switch NOREQ/S, hides possible requesters (IF EXISTS foobar: NOREQ){p}
* Path: Support for multi assign ADD/REMOVE.{p}
* Resident: DEFER/S, program is made resident when first used{p}
* SetEnv: SAVE/S option to permanently save variable in ENVARC:{p}
Support for #! un*x style script execution{p}
Unlimited buffer lengths (command line, variable expansion, quote expansion), no fixed limits{p}
Configurable WShell compatibility features{p}
Fully configurable menus, toolbar, and key shortcuts{p}
On the fly MorphOS->un*x path transformation, if needed{p}
Configurable tab-completion for commands/files/dirs{p}
Review buffer with scrollbar (like KingCON){p}
Powerful Multi pages mode:{p}
* Several shells can run in the same window console.{p}
* Graphical button to switch between them or create new ones{p}.
* Shell can be detached and reattached to another console.{p}
New hook and query functions to internal exec lists
{pp}
{bold}Filesystems{nobold}
{pp}
FastFileSystemII, fully compatible to FastFileSystem{p}
SmartFilesystem{p}
Other filesystems (like PFS3) run emulated {p}
Lowlevel Graphical tools for FFS and SFS (Salvage, Fix in place for damaged volumes, etc...){p}
See Appendix for details.
{pp}
{bold}CDDrive - CDROM filesystem{nobold}
{pp}
ISO9660{p}
Multisession{p}
Rockridge{p}
Joliet
{pp}
{bold}CyberGraphX RTG compatibility{nobold}
{pp}
Ability to use old CyberGraphX v4 drivers (on PowerUP hardware).
{pp}
{bold}Intuition user interface{nobold}
{pp}
Fully skin able GUI, using different bitmap for each element{p}
Shipped with several skins{p}
Opaque Window moving{p}
Window Iconification{p}
Off-screen Windows{p}
screennotify.library{p}
etc...
{pp}
{pp}
{link nws10-3}next page{end}
{pp}